description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced senior midwife to join our highly committed and motivated senior maternity team at the Queen Elizabeth Hospital (QEH) in Kings Lynn.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Currently responsible for the care of approximately 2200 births each year, the service offers choice of care pathway and place of birth to women primarily living in King’s Lynn, West, North and South West Norfolk, and parts of Cambridgeshire, Lincolnshire, &amp; Suffolk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a dynamic, highly motivated and clinically credible senior midwife to lead the core maternity services within QEHKL. Working closely with the Matron ofr continuity maternity services, we are looking for an individual to help shape and develop existing services to ensure all women receive optimal care and support based on their need and personalised care choices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Women’s and Children’s divisional leadership team at QEH is committed to providing a high quality, safe and responsive service to the women we care for. Supporting choice and promoting a philosophy of care that encourages a positive pregnancy and birth experience for women and their families is important to us and we are looking for a like-minded individual to help us further develop our services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are dynamic, passionate about high quality care, thrive on hard work, embrace change and enjoy developing others through strong clinical presence and professional leadership then you might be just the person we are looking for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your commitment we can offer you a supportive work environment, opportunities for wider personal development plus access to education and training programmes to support you in your role and enhance your professional portfolio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amanda Price-Davey Head of Midwifery amanda.price-davey@qehkl.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01553 214787&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion about the role or to arrange a visit to the maternity unit please contact Hannah Barker or Alice Cawte, PA to the Head of Midwifery on 01553 214787 or via email on W&amp;C.Admin@qehkl.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
